anagement experience. \n\nEnjoy our dreams and adventures and \nbecome inspired with your own.\n\nBook Your Show Reservation Now!!!\n\nCraig &amp; Sylvanna \nThe Tahiti Black Pearl Team\n\n(912) 429-5458   \nBlackPearlofTahiti@gmail.com \n\nhttp://www.BlackPearlofTahiti.com \n\nhttp://www.TahitiBlackPearlLegend.com\n&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.blackpearloftahiti.com/resources/Tahiti%20Black%20Pearl%20Floor%20Show%20email.jpg.opt422x341o0,0s422x341.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;center&gt;\n&lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;", "experiences/1/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/1/jobStartedOn": "2-2001", "experiences/1/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/1/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C510BAQHo24CrqXCCgQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631364741589?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=pC2P_j6LaEwHE-Cl6mUO8v04Swed4ZaIwaZvKp_zYwI", "experiences/1/title": "President", "experiences/2/companyId": "509030", "experiences/2/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/2/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/romantic-weddings-of-savannah/", "experiences/2/companyName": "Romantic Weddings Of Savannah", "experiences/2/companySize": "11-50", "experiences/2/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:509030", "experiences/2/companyWebsite": "http://www.RomanticWeddingsOfSavannah.com", "experiences/2/jobDescription": "Our destination weddings exemplify an attitude of \n         &quot;Be a Guest at Your Own Wedding!”\nLeave the details to us on elopements to beach, lighthouse and complete extravagant historic square weddings. Simple receptions to festive  beach luaus or formal historic 1898 Victorian Elegance. Please take a look at our popular wedding websites,\n\n         www.WeddingsbySavannahBeachInn.com\n        www.RomanticWeddingsofSavannah.com\n\nto see why we taken pride in our weddings and, \n\nwww.SavannahBeachInn.com\n\nwhere we have recently been voted: \n \n          &quot;The Most Romantic Inn&quot;\n\nI look forward to your email and phone conversations to more fully \nexplore making your dreams wedding come true!\n\nYour Wedding Planner &amp; Innkeeper   \n\n800 844-1398\n\nemail:  Innkeeper@SavannahBeachInn.com", "experiences/2/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/2/jobStartedOn": "3-2000", "experiences/2/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/2/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQE5393Ppyeogg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631327939852?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=LN8YPZLY16mQQsbqZn7XBVan_F2yY5L6bOK8F5k8nMc", "experiences/2/title": "Director - Operations and Marketing", "experiences/3/companyId": "431132", "experiences/3/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/3/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/pirate-charters-of-the-caribbean/", "experiences/3/companyName": "Pirate Charters Of The Caribbean", "experiences/3/companySize": "51-200", "experiences/3/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:431132", "experiences/3/companyWebsite": "http://www.PirateChartersOfTheCaribbean.com", "experiences/3/jobDescription": "Explore the Virgin Islands on a Sailing or Mega Yacht charter with an experienced and entertaining captain and crew. Although daily reef snorkels, adventures and island romance can be routinely expected, some of the most popular term charters include:\n\nSt John,   US Virgin Islands\n     Most of the island, beaches, shores, and nearby waters are part of a US National Park. Controlled commercialization has kept this paradise in pristine condition with romantic beaches.. \n\nSt Thomas,   US Virgin Islands\n     This economic hub offers an international airport and access to markets and amenities not normally found while pursuing adventure and enjoying romance on the less inhabited other islands.\n\nJost Van Dyke, BVI\nInfamous for the best New Years Eve Parties in the Caribbean, these beaches are magnets to the celebrities and the Rich and Famous of the world.\n\nTortola, BVI \nThis economic hub offers an international airport and access to markets and amenities not normally found while pursuing adventure and enjoying romance on the less inhabited islands.\n\nVirgin Gorda, BVI\nWell known for the “Baths”, a unique geological formation sought by tourists from around the world. These house-sized rock formations naturally arranged to form magnificent beaches and swimming coves second to none.\n\nSalt Island, BVI\n     Known for the magnificent dives on the wreck of the HMS Rhone., \n\nCooper Island, BVI\n     Rub elbows and share some legends and lore with the swashbucklers of the world who dine on this remote private island.\n\nNorman Island, BVI\n     As an inspiration to the book, “Treasure Island” ,and those mindful of pirate booty discovered here in the past, the real treasure is to enjoy snorkeling and diving along the customarily calm waters near the cliffs or “Caves” as the are locally known or the nearby offshore reef structures known as “The Indians", "experiences/3/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/3/jobStartedOn": "2-2000", "experiences/3/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/3/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQF6wFnQG6djWA/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631354925922?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=ira6_r1zRGQDlzoPstqnu8DjBh2xzWVaJh9hTRMh7rc", "experiences/3/title": "CEO", "experiences/4/companyId": "431132", "experiences/4/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/4/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/pirate-charters-of-the-caribbean/", "experiences/4/companyName": "Pirate Charters Of The Caribbean", "experiences/4/companySize": "51-200", "experiences/4/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:431132", "experiences/4/companyWebsite": "http://www.PirateChartersOfTheCaribbean.com", "experiences/4/jobDescription": "Craig Markowski’s solution to the unexpected challenges in life became an enlightening career adventure which has created a small empire of romance and entertainment. Originally from Key Largo and fed up with the deceit he encountered as a successful investment banker on Wall St, he rebuilt his career on his terms. Without deep pockets, he enjoys his travels and works in destinations in which most only dream and shares the experiences like the following:\n\nWith the safety devices removed from the gallows, heart rates throttled as the countdown was blared out and the slow motion cameras rolled. \n\nAs the ending count echoed from the director below, the crack of the hinged platform bashing down on the timber supports attracted the attention of the horrified crowd. While the ensuing flailing dangled bodies swinging at the end of the creaking ropes gave no doubt about the finality of a hanging.\n\nOn cue, a muffled voice from each of the hoods choked out their brief code of reassurance of no sustained injuries much less death from the lynching jolt. The following precious camera moments savored the views that from numerous angles as the stunt doubles’ bodies danced at the end of their nooses in the comfort of safety harnesses. \n\nThis would be Craig Markowski’s second death scene in “The Conspirator” where he shared a lot of non verbal communication with Mary Surratt’s attorney of which she highly respected and befriended. His first death scene is where he consoled Mrs. Mary Todd Lincoln as the President was dying. \n\nWorking through unique careers in Alaska for years of challenging climate and conditions, he accumulated  become a sailboat captain on his “Pirate Charters Of The Caribbean” and a well respected author. With a uniquely positive and determined attitude, he seems almost a legend.\n\nNo adventurous dreams or goals would be complete without generating ideas from his favorite works; “Key West to Alaska” and “Trading Wall St for St John USVI”.", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "12-2009", "experiences/4/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "9-2009", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQF6wFnQG6djWA/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631354925922?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=ira6_r1zRGQDlzoPstqnu8DjBh2xzWVaJh9hTRMh7rc", "experiences/4/title": "Actor & Consultant", "experiences/5/companyId": "431153", "experiences/5/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/5/companyName": "Key West to Alaska", "experiences/5/companySize": "11-50", "experiences/5/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:431153", "experiences/5/companyWebsite": "http://www.KeyWesttoAlaska.com", "experiences/5/jobDescription": "I am extremely grateful for the opportunity to present my book for others to enjoy. I have had a lot of fun in this adventure that probably couldn't even be bought with a winning lottery ticket. As unexpected challenges are met in life, we develop our own blue prints of response. My solution to the challenges became an enlightening career adventure in Alaska. People that I personally share these unusual and unique career stories with quickly become a mesmerized audience of envy. Key West to Alaska allows a break from monotonous routines and also inspire a shining light of hope to those encountering a few unforeseen hurdles in life.\n\nA number of publishers and retailers have expressed quantity interest in the publication for the near future. In  the meantime, Key West to Alaska can be easily purchased in advance of the next printing on www.KeyWesttoAlaska.com .\n\nWhenever you have the opportunity, you are invited to visit me at my current adventure either in Alaska or to come sailing on my recently acquired sailing or mega yacht in the Virgin Islands or on the Georgia coast in the off season. It is also only a matter of time before I look to acquire an inn or resort in the near future of which you are also invited to visit.\n\nSincerely,\n\nCraig Markowski\n\nOperations@KeyWesttoAlaska.com", "experiences/5/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "2-2000", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/5/title": "Author", "experiences/6/companyName": "Savannah Beach Inn", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "Director Operations and Marketing \n\nUtilizing my previous tourism and hospitality experience in directing operations and marketing.  Increased revenue by 400% in the last 36 months with a 95+% occupancy.  Implemented internet and direct marketing processes which have allowed for steady rate increases.  Through revenue management and facility computerization, the high occupancy rates continue as the revenue stream has grown.", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "2000", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/6/title": "Director Operations and Marketing", "experiences/7/companyName": "Savannah Beach Inn", "experiences/7/jobEndedOn": "2009", "experiences/7/jobStartedOn": "2004", "experiences/7/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/7/title": "Weddings", "experiences/8/companyId": "431187", "experiences/8/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/8/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/trading-wall-st-for-st-john-usvi/", "experiences/8/companyName": "Trading Wall St For St John USVI", "experiences/8/companySize": "0-1", "experiences/8/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:431187", "experiences/8/companyWebsite": "http://www.TradingWallStForStJohnUSVI.com", "experiences/8/jobDescription": "Charters in the Virgin Islands\n\nTypically I schedule my sailing charters to begin with the onset of the tropical breezes at around 8:30 am unless my guests like a late start, in which case, an hour more of sleep will usually do the trick. \n\nWhile Buddy, my pet wolf. can hardly wait for the dingy trip to the National Park Service pier to get his business done, I become more fully awake on the quick trip in and also get a chance to check my emails at my booking agent’s nearby marketing kiosk. \n\nBefore motoring back to the sailboat, I’ll get a bag of ice to make my rum punch have a real impression. It doesn't have the customary eleven herbs and spices, but the unique blend of coconut, orange, pineapple, and lime juice sets the mood without an overwhelming taste of the three blends of rum.  Once back on board with everything set, I’ll take to the dingy  back to dock to retrieve the charter guests. My showtime begins with a seamlessly transparent introduction followed by the ride out to the sailboat at anchor.\n\nBy the time that the mooring is released, everyone has been safety oriented and is happily engaged in an activity or conversation.  The transition from Wall St for me had not been easy but I felt a proud sense of accomplishment in completely changing my profession to leave the ethically challenged investment banking world to move on to a saner and stable way of life.\n\nAs a charter captain, my guests include a lot of wannabes and has-beens in the investment issues. To pass the time with them between the snorkel / SCUBA dives and sailing to the nearby foreign islands, I keep the guests entertained with my stories of travels and career challenges. Since so many have lost so much to the Wall Street sharks, I thought to share the experience of my journey here:", "experiences/8/jobEndedOn": "1-2009", "experiences/8/jobLocationCountry": "US", "experiences/8/jobStartedOn": "2-2004", "experiences/8/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/8/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E0BAQHPRAJXRZUFUg/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631318609881?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=E-d2ox4fCw1wbKW_Jj75FbXfynvyTrPQfUjySD5idno", "experiences/8/title": "Author", "experiences/9/companyName": "Ocean Plaza Beach Resort", "experiences/9/jobEndedOn": "1-2009", "experiences/9/jobStartedOn": "2001", "experiences/9/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/9/title": "Wedding Planner & Marketing Projects", "experiences/10/companyName": "Spirit Of Olde Savannah", "experiences/10/jobDescription": "Spirit Of Olde Savannah®\n\nEnjoy a Production of Savannah’s Charming Rich History.\n\nNancy Hillis, immortalized as Mandy Nichols in the ‘Midnight Garden of the Good and Evil©’, appeals to crowds again with her Southern Charm. Singing and entertaining while the Spirit of Olde Savannah® and cast share the history of our fair city with multi-media effects of included historic city and Civil War photo videos. The downtown shows will include a Low-Country Shrimp Boil  lunch, initially for Wed. thru Sat. afternoons and look forward to expanded routine daily schedules with additional evening concepts. For more info, \n\nemail: Spirit@SpiritOfOldeSavannah.com\n\nBook it Now!", "experiences/10/jobEndedOn": "12-2008", "experiences/10/jobStartedOn": "2-2006", "experiences/10/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/10/title": "Producer", "experiences/11/companyName": "Gourmet Solutions", "experiences/11/jobEndedOn": "9-2008", "experiences/11/jobStartedOn": "2001", "experiences/11/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/11/title": "Wedding Planner / Photography Packages", "experiencesCount": "12", "firstName": "Craig", "firstRoleYear": "2000", "followers": "671", "fullName": "Craig Markowski", "headline": "President at Tahiti Black Pearl", "isCreator": "false", "isCurrentlyEmployed": "true", "isInfluencer": "false", "isJobSeeker": "false", "isPremium": "false", "isRetired": "false", "isVerified": "false", "jobLocation": "Ft Lauderdale, FL 33305 USA", "jobStartedOn": "1-2015", "jobStillWorking": "true", "jobTitle": "Co-Founder", "lastName": "Markowski", "linkedinId": "50352428", "linkedinPublicUrl": "https://linkedin.com/in/keywesttoalaska", "linkedinUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/keywesttoalaska", "openConnection": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADMyJXYBl3rXeArW1gxoaDM6vDxwR9xWbQc", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/first_name": "Rashid", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/follower_count": "40", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/headline": "Imports & Trading Spices", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/last_name": "Kanchwala", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/0/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms